      {
        "id": 2293498,
        "name": "Max Kelly",
        "username": "Max_K",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/max_k/{size}/2700_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-11-08T15:12:31.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for all who\u2019ve chimed in. Appreciate being waved off what could otherwise have been some poor investments based on reputation. It\u2019s particularly interesting to me that A) these vignerons are willing to risk their good names this way, and B) that Van Canneyt\u2019s style for his n\u00e9goce wines sounds so different from what he crafts at H-N. His family\u2019s restraining influence?</p>\n<p>PS Charlie - your CvC acronym through me for a loop for a minute. In my world, it\u2019s reserved for Carl von Clausewitz, the Prussian strategist.</p>",
