      {
        "id": 2293669,
        "name": "Gerhard P.  (P r @ \u20ac s e n t)",
        "username": "Gerhard_P",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/8baadc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-11-08T18:20:18.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Ian Dorin\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Ian Dorin:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I\u2019m definitely in the camp of \u201cnot worth the money\u201d, unfortunately. I want to like the wines, but the price of these wines often outpaces the Domaine wines, which is bizarre.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>FWIW - in early Sept. I watched the transport of a freshly pressed barrel (228 l) of Corton-Charlemagne 2017 must that a small domaine (with even a smaller additional negociant-business) has just purchased (and they had to provide the new barrel themselves).<br>\nI asked how much it was: \"we don\u00b4t know yet, the price has to be established only after the harvest, but last year it was 16000 \u20ac).</p>\n<p>At app. 290 bottles that\u00b4s more than 55 \u20ac per bottle for the must alone \u2026  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/c/ce2642e7caade9035e3a3b13c8b8d2b3ddb2b4c9.gif\" width=\"43\" height=\"54\" alt=\"flirtysmile\" title=\"[flirtysmile.gif]\" class=\"animated\"><br>\n+18 months of elevage, bottle, cork, label, capsule, cases \u2026+ TVA 20% \u2026 I don\u00b4t think they earned a lot with it \u2026</p>",
        "post_number": 13,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 13,
